summary: Completed comprehensive frontend testing of TripCost Vanilla JS SPA. All 11 required features tested and working perfectly including homepage, navigation, destinations page, city pages, calculator functionality, nomad rankings, and 404 handling.
passed_tests: Homepage loads with hero, features, and top 6 city cards
Navigation works between all pages via data-link attributes
/destinations page shows all 19 cities with scores and monthly costs
/city/new-york shows city hero, stats, cost breakdown with USD currency
/city/lisbon shows correct EUR currency (11 EUR symbols found)
/calculator page has working dropdowns for city, housing, lifestyle
/calculator updates values when changing city selection (Bali shows $2,365)
/calculator updates when changing housing from center ($2,365) to suburb ($1,705)
/calculator updates when changing lifestyle from standard ($1,705) to premium ($2,860)
/nomad page shows ranked table of all 19 cities with scores, WiFi, coworking costs
404 page shows for invalid routes like /invalid-page with working 'Go Home' button
